description:
&lt;p&gt;FIXED TERM POSITION FOR 12 MONTHS FOR MATERNITY LEAVE COVER&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Paediatric Speech and Language Therapist who would like to work as part of an innovative, forward thinking team with inspirational children?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then we have the perfect role for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Speech and Language Therapist, who has considerable knowledge and experience of working in a range of community settings. Applicants will have knowledge and experience of working with children of all ages and who have a range of speech, language and communication needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will essentially support the children in our Early Years and Complex needs service. Firstly, The post holder will be working in our special schools in the Vale Royal area – specifically Hebden Green and Russett. Both are outstanding special schools which offer a supportive and enjoyable working environment alongside one of our clinical specialist therapists, and as part of the wider MDT. Secondly, The post holder may also be required to work as part of our complex needs / Early years team across the same locality. This will involve assessment and treatment of children within early years settings, or their home environment, with close working alongside other members of the MDT including early years staff, Health visitors and paediatricians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Speech and Language Therapy team are a supportive, innovative and forward thinking team. Experienced colleagues and the locality team manager are always readily available for support where needed. The post holder will be an integral part of a small supportive team where training and personal development is also encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like the role for you, please do not hesitate to contact us!&lt;/p&gt;
